{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Facet"], "type": "title", "extent": [0, 10], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [108, 165], "text": ["Controls the smoothness of faceting of a surface."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [165, 229], "text": ["This node also lets you consolidate points or surface normals."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [229, 589], "text": ["Facet, like Divide, works as a pipeline to change geometry in stages.\nFor this reason, Compute Normals appears twice. For example, you can\ncompute surface normals before making any points shared by different\npolygons unique, which gives you the unusual result of smooth shading\nand unique point, as the normals get computed while the points are still\nshared."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [589, 767], "text": ["This tool is useful for cleaning up polygons. You can reorient back-facing polygons, remove degenerative polygons, consolidate or unique points, or cusp polygon based on edges."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [772, 908], "text": ["This op is great for cleaning up geometry read in from ", {"text": [".dxf"], "type": "em"}, " files.\n    It corrects flipped normals present in some ", {"text": [".dxf"], "type": "em"}, " files."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "tip", "extent": [767, 772]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "tip_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "extent": [926, 1008], "text": ["Select the faces, edges, or points you want to facet."]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1103, 1200], "text": ["You can change the facet specifications in the ", {"text": ["parameter editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/panes/parms", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/ref/panes/parms"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Click the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/SOP/facet", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SOP/facet"}, {"text": ["Facet"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/facet", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/facet"}, " tool on the ", {"text": ["Polygon"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."], "extent": [1008, 1103], "blevel": 2, "type": "ord"}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1200, 1234], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/facet.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/facet.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Using Facet"], "extent": [908, 926], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1254, 1288], "text": ["Subset of geometry to facet."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Group"], "role": "item", "extent": [1246, 1254], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1309, 1359], "text": ["Computes normals based on incoming geometry."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Pre-Compute Normals"], "role": "item", "extent": [1288, 1309], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1385, 1437], "text": ["Resizes the incoming normals to a length of 1."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Make Normals Unit Length"], "role": "item", "extent": [1359, 1385], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1452, 1546], "text": ["Creates new points for any vertices sharing a point so that\n    points will be unshared."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Unique Points"], "role": "item", "extent": [1437, 1452], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1580, 1619], "text": ["Points are not fused together."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [1560, 1580], "text": ["No Consolidate"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1653, 1733], "text": ["Points within a specified distance of each other share a\n        point."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [1619, 1653], "text": ["Consolidate Points Slow/Fast"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1768, 1867], "text": ["Points within a specified distance of each other have their\n        normals averaged."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [1733, 1768], "text": ["Consolidate Normals Slow/Fast"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1877, 2000], "text": ["The slow versions of consolidation should not be used. They\n        are for backwards compatibility only."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "note", "extent": [1867, 1877]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Consolidate"], "role": "item", "extent": [1546, 1560], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2025, 2068], "text": ["Threshold distance for consolidation."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Distance"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "dist"}, "extent": [2000, 2010], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2110, 2312], "text": ["Forces Distance to represent consolidate distances accurately,\n    and forces consolidation to be performed in order of point\n    number, to avoid moving points to within Distance of other points."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Use Accurate Distance"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "accurate"}, "extent": [2068, 2091], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2334, 2435], "text": ["Remove points from polygons if they lie on the line connecting\n    the previous and next point."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Remove Inline Points"], "role": "item", "extent": [2312, 2334], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2466, 2508], "text": ["Threshold distance for collinearity."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Distance"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "inlinedist"}, "extent": [2435, 2445], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2525, 2569], "text": ["Winds all polygons the same direction."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Orient Polygons"], "role": "item", "extent": [2508, 2525], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2584, 2868], "text": ["Creates hard edges between adjacent sides by uniquing points when the\n    edge angle exceeds ", {"text": ["Cusp Angle"], "type": "ui"}, ".  Using a ", {"text": ["Normal node"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/normal", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/normal"}, "\n    to compute vertex normals may be preferable, since uniquing points\n    of a watertight mesh will make it no longer watertight."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Cusp Polygons"], "role": "item", "extent": [2569, 2584], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2896, 2929], "text": ["Threshold angle to cusp at."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Cusp Angle"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "angle"}, "extent": [2868, 2880], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2948, 2992], "text": ["Cleans up any degenerate polygons."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Remove Degenerate"], "role": "item", "extent": [2929, 2948], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3005, 3081], "text": ["Flattens each of the polygons so their points lie along a plane.  "]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Make Planar"], "role": "item", "extent": [2992, 3005], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3103, 3160], "text": ["Computes normals based on result of this operation."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Post-Compute Normals"], "role": "item", "extent": [3081, 3103], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3177, 3283], "text": ["Reverses the direction of all of the point normals.  Performed\n    after all the other computations."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Reverse Normals"], "role": "item", "extent": [3160, 3177], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [1234, 1246], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3292, 3313], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/normal", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/normal"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3313, 3331], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/fuse", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/fuse"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3331, 3353], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/edgecusp", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/edgecusp"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [3283, 3292], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Controls the smoothness of faceting of a surface."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "tags": "cusp, normals, edges, points", "namespace": null, "internal": "facet", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "SOP/facet"}, "title": ["Facet"]}